item.title: what next?
item.description: Finally have some time to think about the past weeks. Michel Foucault: I donâ€™t feel that it is necessary to know exactly what I am. The main interest in life and work is to become someone else that you were not in the beginning. If you knew when you began a book what you would say at the end, do you think that you would have the courage to write it?
